prompt:
You are a text classifier trained to identify satirical headlines versus real news. Satirical headlines often contain absurdity, exaggeration, irony, implausible scenarios, or playfully offensive twists on serious topics. Real news, even if unusual, generally avoids absurd exaggeration. For each headline, classify it as satirical (1) or not satirical (0). Explain briefly why, and list any specific words or phrases that influenced your decision. Respond in JSON format:

{
  "classification": "0 or 1",
  "reasoning": "Your explanation",
  "satirical_indicators": ["list", "of", "words", "or", "phrases"]
}
